attribution.changeMessage: Her death certificate states that she died 8 July 1853 at Albion Road in the sub-district of Woolwich Dockyard, district of Greenwich, Kent County.

The Union Chapel Register of Burials in Woolwich, Kent 1850-1854, found at Ancestry.com in the England & Wales, Non-Conformist and Non-Parochial Registers, 1567-1970, show that Margret Griffith was buried 11 July 1853.

See sources listed below: Birth and christening record indicates Liverpool.  LDS Church records in Woolwich, Kent, England indicate that he was born in Liverpool and emigrated in 1856 which is consistent with joining the Martin Handcart Company.  The 1851 census also says he was born in Liverpool.  EDMUND STREET OR GREAT CROSS HALL STREET INDEPENDENCE:

Just changing date to standard form. -Deb

See the England Births and Christenings listed below which indicate he was born and christened in Liverpool.  LDS Church records in Woolwich, Kent, England indicate that he was born in Liverpool and emigrated in 1856 which is consistent with joining the Martin Handcart Company.  The 1851 census also says he was born in Liverpool.  There are many John Griffiths in Wales and England but to me the evidence listed in the records point to this John has being born in Liverpool.
